com.jensen.Controller.managers

Class QueryManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.jensen.Controller.managers.QueryManager

  • public class QueryManager
extends java.lang.Object
    This Class holds all the necessary methods and variables for the database connection. It also currently holds a few methods which updates the View with the correct data asked for [The latter will be fixed in the near future].
    Author:
    Kami Hassanzadeh, Gustav Malm

      • QueryManager

        public QueryManager(org.hibernate.Session session,
                    javax.swing.table.DefaultTableModel model)
        This is the Constructor for the Class QueryManager. Takes in a DefaultTableModel object as well as a Session Object through 2 (two) parameters.
        Parameters:
        session - This parameter is used to set this Class's database connection. Parameter value taken from Application.Class
        model - This parameter is used to update this Class's DefaultTableModel reference. [Required due to the current design but will be fixed properly to follow a better MVC-Design Pattern in the near future.]
